In his continued charm offensive against his political opponents, Mr Ruto hopes to put his house in order in what he believes will lay a road map for a strong support base in the region come 2022.
The DP met the about 20 leaders from Kisii County at his Karen residence in Nairobi led by Kisii deputy governor Joash Maangi, MPs Silvanus Osoro (South Mugirango) and Alpha Miruka (Bomachoge Chache).
Unite leaders
Former Constitutional Implementation Commission chairman Charles Nyachae, former Kenya Ports Authority managing director Daniel Manduku and former Bonchari MP Zebedeo Opore were the other attendants.



