Mr Maangi, Ruto’s pointman in Gusii, said the meeting was meant to unite leaders allied to the DP.
The Thursday meeting was also meant to lay political strategies post-Covid-19. This is after the DP counselled a series of meetings in the region last month due to the health crisis.
“The DP had organised at least eight meetings in Kisii last month. But Covid-19 cases increased and he had to stop. He has agreed to proceed with the meetings as soon as infections reduce,” said Mr Maangi.
The deputy governor said though the leaders who met the DP support him, they differ on a number of issues amongst them the Building Bridges Initiative.



