Support BBI
“For example, I support the BBI, Mr Nyachae does not. The meeting reminded us that our goal was DP’s support and that is where we should focus,” said Mr Maangi.
Another issue is Mr Maangi’s support for Interior Cabinet Secretary Fred Matiang’i.
“Many are wondering why I was in Karen the other day, just a month after declaring my support for our son, Dr Matiang’i. The CS has not declared interest for presidency, Ruto has. There is no conflict there. I support Matiang’i in his bid to unite our Abagusii community,” said Mr Maangi.
Just last month, Mr Maangi pledged to work with Dr Matiang’i in what he said will help galvanise the unity of Abagusii.
In a surprise move that has left his supporters in confusion, analysts said the political about-turn by Mr Maangi was a blow to Mr Ruto, who has been banking on him to get support in Gusii.
Mr Maangi made the unexpected declaration in Nyagesenda SDA church, in Kitutu Chache North, during a function attended by his boss, Governor James Ongwae, the man he's had on and off relationship.
